"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"## Creation is actually good for you. Do it every day.\\n\\n[![ScottCDunn](https://miro.medium.com/fit/c/56/56/1\\\\*33AQXVKvWWUL5Ka5Hd4Rzg.jpeg)](https://scottcdunn.medium.com/?source=post_page-----85498e3e5b25-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[](https://scottcdunn.medium.com/?source=post_page-----85498e3e5b25-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[ScottCDunn](https://scottcdunn.medium.com/?source=post_page-----85498e3e5b25-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[](https://medium.com/creators-hub/id-like-to-be-free-of-it-now-85498e3e5b25?source=post_page-----85498e3e5b25-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[Dec 16·5 min read](https://medium.com/creators-hub/id-like-to-be-free-of-it-now-85498e3e5b25?source=post_page-----85498e3e5b25-----------------------------------)\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/1\\\\*gGUvcaHeltGrWzTa69AprQ.jpeg)\\n\\nPhoto: Matthieu Spohn/Getty Images\\n\\nAddictions are usually addictions to consumption. I’m no stranger to addiction. I’ve tried pot, booze, people, sex, food, caffeine, histrionics, TV, and news scrolling. I’ve tasted many things to alter my mood and every one of them came up empty. In the end, it’s still up to me to be happy. No matter how I try to alter my…\\n\",\"timestamp\":1640431517,\"title\":\"How to Get Addicted to Writing - Creators Hub - Medium\"},\"digest\":\"eSnHThEBLjfyEQ2xW7PL9R49TRguG-4v22ecMp6tguQ\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xA39AA6b4FC56B563988A098541De388Bd70AB11d\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"NNqxSe2i_idN-0wBYeWDvRKEjIMnJp4PouM5kkvsZGo\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"y0thJE1rK1wRP-awojztyOBdxDnXsxxV_yNixugzxO8\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"ehV7xZa5uzQaQTgDeswR7OV2wP-mjVSkIAkqkhWcwTvg11Nx1JlUFjeInRHepkCWrqYMR8RjCrcgcsxHVnbz6Q\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xd355087656610b8dd2546112e03efeef2c53ee7c3df1235ad34f01a79a9e27ba47cb712571d983122e3efa554e5bfab49961a13381fb9520988